case_address_found_1: In street in front of 2149 Reyburn Rd.
case_circumstances: On October 18, 1986, at approximately 6:34 a.m., members of  Cleveland Heights Police Department received an assignment to respond to the intersection of Reyburn and Westburn Roads.  On arrival, the body of a black female was located in the street, opposite 2149 Reyburn Rd.  Further investigation revealed the unidentified black female was apparently pushed from a westbound automobile and had been shot at another location.
